WEBVTT

00:03.420 --> 00:05.079
- Hey!
- Hey, Dad.

00:05.080 --> 00:06.279
Hey, Dad.

00:06.280 --> 00:08.309
You coming with us to visit
Becky at the hospital?

00:08.310 --> 00:09.959
No, I can't. I'm on a break from work,

00:09.960 --> 00:12.119
but I got something for Becky,
if you'd give it to her.

00:12.120 --> 00:13.979
The store sells this really great

00:13.980 --> 00:16.517
Lanolin cocoa butter for stretch marks.

00:17.980 --> 00:19.269
Wow, that's sweet.

00:19.270 --> 00:21.599
After all she's been through,
it's nice to remind her

00:21.600 --> 00:23.519
she's all stretched out.

00:23.520 --> 00:25.639
I looked in our baby section.

00:25.640 --> 00:28.194
It was either that or something
for cracked nipples.

00:28.195 --> 00:29.947
They crack?

00:31.880 --> 00:34.669
I gotta go. My manager's
in a terrible mood.

00:34.670 --> 00:36.703
He tanked his SATs.

00:36.704 --> 00:37.989
Bye.

00:37.990 --> 00:40.019
If Becky's getting
something, we should bring

00:40.020 --> 00:41.479
something for Lil Bev.

00:41.480 --> 00:43.279
- Like a stuffed animal.
- Mm-hmm.

00:43.280 --> 00:44.779
I don't know. It's a preemie.

00:44.780 --> 00:46.279
A Beanie Baby that's
bigger than your kid...

00:46.280 --> 00:48.699
that's gonna be depressing.

00:50.130 --> 00:52.439
Darlene, it's your phone.

00:52.440 --> 00:54.679
It's Mark's school.

00:54.680 --> 00:55.769
Wow!

00:55.770 --> 00:57.689
Are you in trouble,
or does the pink-eye girl

00:57.690 --> 00:59.184
have lice now?

01:01.820 --> 01:03.319
Hello?

01:03.320 --> 01:05.357
Uh, hi, Principal Reynolds. How are you?

01:05.358 --> 01:07.400
Oh.

01:08.170 --> 01:10.309
Uh-huh.

01:10.310 --> 01:12.156
Okay, that's... that's not good.

01:12.157 --> 01:15.359
Um, yeah. We'll be there.

01:15.360 --> 01:16.760
What's he in trouble for?

01:16.770 --> 01:20.288
Spreading too much sunshine
everywhere he goes?

01:20.289 --> 01:23.167
Why don't you guys head out to
the car and give us a second?

01:24.940 --> 01:27.919
So, we have to go see
the principal tomorrow

01:27.920 --> 01:30.639
because your school has a "no PDA" rule

01:30.640 --> 01:32.929
and somebody posted a
picture of you kissing

01:32.930 --> 01:35.169
your friend Austin at school.

01:35.170 --> 01:37.869
He wins at everything,
and now he has a boyfriend?

01:37.870 --> 01:38.880
I hate you!

01:40.880 --> 01:43.339
So, Austin's your boyfriend?

01:43.340 --> 01:44.897
How come you didn't tell me?

01:44.898 --> 01:47.919
I don't know. I guess he's my boyfriend.

01:47.920 --> 01:49.799
When we found out they
were gonna start serving

01:49.800 --> 01:51.019
personal pizzas at lunch,

01:51.020 --> 01:53.020
we got so excited that we kissed.

01:54.490 --> 01:56.670
I get that.

01:57.701 --> 02:01.219
Well, there is a longer talk to come,

02:01.220 --> 02:04.123
but have you guys done
anything more than kiss?

02:04.124 --> 02:05.699
No, just the kiss.

02:05.700 --> 02:07.439
And that was the first time.

02:07.440 --> 02:09.378
He only told me he was gay last week.

02:09.380 --> 02:12.039
Is Austin the dark, brooding one

02:12.040 --> 02:15.419
or the kid that's always
smelling his hand?

02:15.420 --> 02:16.960
Neither, Grandpa.

02:18.097 --> 02:19.339
All right, well, we'll
deal with this tomorrow,

02:19.340 --> 02:21.519
but in the meantime, no more PDA.

02:21.520 --> 02:23.559
You're at school to
learn, not kiss, okay?

02:23.560 --> 02:25.240
Got it.

02:26.480 --> 02:30.608
So, you think you're ready for
a relationship, huh, pal?

02:30.609 --> 02:33.237
I think so. Is there
anything I should know?

02:33.238 --> 02:37.519
I'll just say, you're 12,
don't sign anything,

02:37.520 --> 02:40.368
and just treat him the way you'd
want to be treated, I guess.

02:40.369 --> 02:42.495
Austin says I don't listen enough.

02:42.496 --> 02:44.369
Does he also say you drink too much?

02:44.370 --> 02:45.749
'Cause that's coming.

02:48.627 --> 02:50.962
How are we doing?

02:50.963 --> 02:54.580
I've been trying to pump every
couple hours, but nothing.

02:55.718 --> 02:57.239
I've always been able
to count on my boobs,

02:57.240 --> 02:58.840
but they're betraying me.

03:00.472 --> 03:02.515
Have you tried to express
the milk by hand?

03:02.516 --> 03:03.749
Are you kidding?

03:03.750 --> 03:07.687
I've been squeezing myself
like an entitled frat boy.

03:07.688 --> 03:10.189
It takes some people longer.

03:10.190 --> 03:11.733
Everything'll be okay.

03:11.734 --> 03:15.499
As Becky's life and birth coach,

03:15.500 --> 03:17.159
um, I need to inform you

03:17.160 --> 03:20.199
that your constant
reductive reassurances

03:20.200 --> 03:21.699
are not appreciated.

03:21.700 --> 03:24.519
She understands that the
milk contains colostrum,

03:24.520 --> 03:26.080
which carries the antibodies

03:26.081 --> 03:28.109
that preemies need to fight disease.

03:28.110 --> 03:30.019
She knows that she's playing
with the baby's life.

03:30.020 --> 03:31.960
So just let her be, could ya?

03:33.200 --> 03:35.210
I got your back.

03:39.120 --> 03:40.219
Hey.

03:40.220 --> 03:42.099
Hey! Did you see the baby?

03:42.100 --> 03:45.390
- Oh, yeah. Strong.
- She looks beautiful!

03:46.560 --> 03:48.599
Don't sugarcoat it.

03:48.600 --> 03:50.646
I've seen her. You can be honest.

03:50.647 --> 03:53.359
Okay, well, I've seen cuter
babies in jars at the fair.

03:54.651 --> 03:58.069
It's okay. Babies don't
always start out pretty.

03:58.070 --> 04:01.169
Darlene looked like Yoda.
You had Dumbo ears.

04:01.170 --> 04:02.320
And DJ...

04:03.260 --> 04:04.779
DJ did start out pretty,

04:04.780 --> 04:07.700
so... be careful what you wish for.

04:08.874 --> 04:11.739
Hey, Beck, you know,
you've been up for two nights.

04:11.740 --> 04:13.819
It's hard to make milk when
you're tired and stressed.

04:13.820 --> 04:14.829
You need to sleep.

04:14.830 --> 04:17.279
Geena's hospital...
they had a lactation specialist.

04:17.279 --> 04:18.507
Maybe you can get one of those.

04:18.509 --> 04:19.678
This is County.

04:19.680 --> 04:22.304
People pay their bills
here with chickens.

04:22.305 --> 04:24.597
We have chickens!

04:24.598 --> 04:27.269
You don't have chickens.

04:27.270 --> 04:29.186
